				  PLATEAU 2014  

				 
                	 October 25, 2014   Thomas visited rainy Portland to co-chair the Fifth Workshop on the Evaluation and Usability of Programming Languages and Tools at SPLASH 2014. There were many great talks on topics ranging from making programming more social through newsfeeds to an analysis of how race detection tools benefit developers. Josh Bloch, designer of the Java collections framework […] 
				 

				   Posted in   Uncategorized  |     Comments Off  on PLATEAU 2014    

			 

				 
				  UIST 2014  

				 
                	 October 8, 2014   Thomas attended UIST 2014 in Honolulu, presenting his paper on Microtask programming: building software with a crowd. There were a number of interesting papers related to programming tools and crowdsourcing. SDCL also had an entry in the UIST 2014 Analog Fabrication Sandcastle Competition. 
				 

				   Posted in   Travel  |     Comments Off  on UIST 2014    

			 

				 
				  Welcome Arturo and Fabio  

				 
                	 September 15, 2014   Welcome Arturo Di Lecce and Fabio Ricci! Arturo and Fabio join us from Politecnico di Milano in Italy, where they are currently masters students. They’ll be visiting SDCL in sunny California for the next year and will be working on projects related to crowd programming and crowd design. 
				 

				   Posted in   News  |     Comments Off  on Welcome Arturo and Fabio    

			 

				 
				  Crowd Programming featured on ACM TechNews  

				 
                	 July 30, 2014   Our work on Crowd Programming was also featured on ACM TechNews and Techwire.net. 
				 

				   Posted in   News  |     Comments Off  on Crowd Programming featured on ACM TechNews    

			 

				 
