				  Congratulations to the UC Irvine Design Competition Winners!  

				 
                	 July 7, 2014   Congratulations to Ulyana Skladchikova and Matias Giorgio, two of the winners in the UC Irvine Software Design Competition. Participants first produced a design – describing either a system’s architecture and design or its user experience – and were then given some of the designs produced by others, producing a second revised design incorporating insights they […] 
				 

				   Posted in   News  |     Comments Off  on Congratulations to the UC Irvine Design Competition Winners!    

			 

				 
				  Grant on Crowd Programming  

				 
                	 June 13, 2014   We’re very happy to announce that the National Science Foundation has awarded SDCL a $1.4M grant to investigate the application of microtask crowdsourcing to programming. More details in the official NSF announcement. 
				 

				   Posted in   News  |     Comments Off  on Grant on Crowd Programming    

			 

				 
				  ICSE 2014  

				 
                	 June 13, 2014   Two members of SDCL – André and Thomas – attended ICSE 2014 in Hyderabad, India. André served as a Program Chair of ICSE, helping to select the program of ICSE. Thomas served as an organizer of a new workshop on Crowdsourcing in Software Engineering (CSI-SE). Both ICSE and CSI-SE went very well, and we had […] 
				 

				   Posted in   conference ,  Travel  |     Comments Off  on ICSE 2014    

			 

				 
				  SCALE meeting at UC Irvine  

				 
                	 May 16, 2014   UC Irvine hosted a meeting of the SCALE research group. SDCL had posters on several research projects. Lots of great discussion! 
				 

				   Posted in   News  |     Comments Off  on SCALE meeting at UC Irvine    

			 

				 
